        %iframe{:src => "https://player.vimeo.com/video/68357859", :style => "position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;"}
      .two-col.grid-span
        %p I was usually assigned a "shot" or maybe a group of related "shots" at a time. My task was to come up with what the rendering and animation of a particular effect like fire would look like in a shot. We would often scour YouTube for reference or shoot our own.
        %p After an initial pass, I would present to the Head of Effects and would iterate on that feedback. Eventually the Visual Effects Supervisor and Director(s) would get involved until it was final.
        %p At DreamWorks, effects artists integrate their own effects (composite) with the renders from the lighting department.
      .one-col{:style => "width: 100%; padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;"}
        %iframe{:src => "https://player.vimeo.com/video/81429709", :style => "position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;"}
